<TEI.2><text><body><div1 type="alphabetic letter" n="F" org="uniform" sample="complete"><entryFree key="Fondly" type="main" opt="n"><orth extent="full" opt="n">Fondly,</orth> 1) foolishly: <bibl n="shak. luc 207" default="NO" valid="yes">Lucr. 207</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. err 4.2.57" default="NO" valid="yes">Err. IV, 2, 57</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. shr 4.2.31" default="NO" valid="yes">Shr. IV, 2, 31</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. jn 2.258" default="NO" valid="yes">John II, 258</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. r2 3.3.185" default="NO" valid="yes">R2 III, 3, 185</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. 2h4 4.2.119" default="NO" valid="yes">H4B IV, 2, 119</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. 3h6 2.2.38" default="NO" valid="yes">H6C II, 2, 38</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. r3 3.7.147" default="NO" valid="yes">R3 III, 7, 147</bibl>.<lb />2) in a trifling, nugatory manner: <cit><quote>how f. dost thou spur a forward horse,</quote> <bibl n="shak. r2 4.72" default="NO" valid="yes">R2 IV, 72</bibl></cit>. Perhaps also in <bibl n="shak. r3 3.7.147" default="NO" valid="yes">R3 III, 7, 147</bibl>.
<lb />3) tenderly: <bibl n="shak. r2 3.2.9" default="NO" valid="yes">R2 III, 2, 9</bibl>.
</entryFree></div1></body></text></TEI.2>